 Lily James, 32, wore a sophisticated yet striking pastel pink number on the red carpet. The Spring-inspired Versace dress had a thigh-high split which showed off her toned legs. The dress was also low cut and had floral details. At the Dolby Theatre in Hollywood, Lily looked stunning in baby pink. The Pam & Tommy star is presenting at the Oscars awards ceremony. She told Sky News: “This is my first Oscars. It’s so special that we are all able to all be together.” Lily accessorised her red carpet look with a glamorous diamond necklace. She wore her brunette hair down in an effortlessly glamorous style.   